      "text": [
        ": أَیُّمَا مُؤْمِنٍ حَبَسَ مُؤْمِناً عَنْ مَالِهِ وَ هُوَ مُحْتَاجٌ إِلَیْهِ لَمْ یَذُقْ وَ اللَّهِ مِنْ طَعَامِ الْجَنَّهِ وَ لَا یَشْرَبُ مِنَ الرَّحِیقِ الْمَخْتُومِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "2. And from the previous chain from Muhammad b. Sinan from al-Muffadhal from Abi Abdillah (a.s.) who said: “One who withholds the wealth of a believer which he needed, by Allah, he will never taste the food of Paradise nor will he be able to taste the sealed drink of Paradise.”"
        ]
      }
